     62          /**
     63           *  @brief      This API manages the External Interrupts
     64           *              All the pins of the STM32F0x micro controller are configured as External Interrupt
     65           *              All the similar PORT pin indexs are connected to that indexed external interrupt
     66           *              For Example - PORTA.PIN0, PORTB.PIN0, PORTC.PIN0, PORTD.PIN0, PORTE.PIN0...all are connected to EXTI0_IRQ_CHANNEL
     67           *                            PORTA.PIN1, PORTB.PIN1, PORTC.PIN1, PORTD.PIN1, PORTE.PIN1...all are connected to EXTI1_IRQ_CHANNEL
     68           *
     69           *              This drives the hardware limitation - All the External interrupt pins should have different pin number(No more than one same index pin is allowed)
     70           *
     71           *              Based on the External interrupt pin index use the ExtInterrupt__Ext() function for handling the ISR's for example -
     72           *              If the external interrupt is configured for PORTA, PIN0 and PORTC, PIN12 then the InterruptVector_prv.h file shall look like this -
     73           *              #define EXTI0_IRQHANDLER                IntMgr__ExtInterruptExt   //This handles the EXT0 IRQ for PORTA.PIN0
     74          */

